## Development Patterns

### Backend Patterns

**Dependency Injection (TypeDI)**

All services and repositories use TypeDI container:

```typescript
import { Service } from "typedi";

@Service()
export class AccountService {
  constructor(
    private readonly accountRepository: AccountRepository,
    private readonly userRepository: UserRepository
  ) {}
}
```

**Repository Pattern**

All data access extends BaseRepository:

```typescript
@Service()
export class AccountRepository extends BaseRepository<Account> {
  constructor(db: PostgresJsDatabase<typeof schema>) {
    super(db, schema.accounts);
  }

  async findByUserId(userId: string, tx?: DrizzleTransaction) {
    const database = tx ?? this.db;
    return database.query.accounts.findMany({
      where: eq(schema.accounts.userId, userId),
    });
  }
}
```

**Use Cases**

Complex operations use explicit use case classes:

```typescript
@Service()
export class CreateHoldingsWithDependenciesUseCase {
  async execute(input: CreateHoldingInput) {
    // Multi-step business logic
    // Transaction management
    // Error handling
  }
}
```

**tRPC Procedures**

API endpoints use tRPC with Zod validation:

```typescript
export const accountRouter = router({
  getByUserId: protectedProcedure.query(async ({ ctx }) => {
    return accountService.findByUserId(ctx.user.id);
  }),

  create: protectedProcedure
    .input(createAccountSchema)
    .mutation(async ({ input, ctx }) => {
      return accountService.create(input, ctx.user.id);
    }),
});
```

### Web Frontend Patterns

**Component Composition**

Build features from smaller components:

```typescript
export function AccountsPage() {
  return (
    <div className="container">
      <AccountsHeader />
      <AccountsList />
      <CreateAccountDialog />
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Form Validation**

Use React Hook Form with Zod:

```typescript
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";

const form = useForm({
  resolver: zodResolver(createAccountSchema),
  defaultValues: { name: "", institutionId: "" },
});
```

**Data Fetching**

Use tRPC React Query:

```typescript
import { trpc } from "@/lib/trpc";

export function AccountsList() {
  const { data: accounts, isLoading } = trpc.accounts.getByUserId.useQuery();

  if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />;
  return <div>{/* Render accounts */}</div>;
}
```

### Mobile Patterns

**Ignite Theming System (MANDATORY)**

All styles use ThemedStyle functions:

```typescript
import { useAppTheme } from "@/theme/context";
import type { ThemedStyle } from "@/theme/types";

export const MyComponent: FC = () => {
  const { themed, theme } = useAppTheme();

  return (
    <View style={themed($container)}>
      <Text style={themed($title)}>Title</Text>
    </View>
  );
};

const $container: ThemedStyle<ViewStyle> = ({ spacing, colors }) => ({
  padding: spacing.md,
  backgroundColor: colors.background,
});

const $title: ThemedStyle<TextStyle> = ({ typography, colors }) => ({
  ...typography.heading,
  color: colors.text,
});
```

**Internationalization (MANDATORY)**

All user-facing text uses tx props:

```typescript
// Use tx prop (NOT translate() function)
<Text tx="common:welcome" />
<Button tx="actions:submit" onPress={handleSubmit} />

// With interpolation
<Text tx="profile:greeting" txOptions={{ name: userName }} />

// Translation file structure (en.ts, ru.ts)
{
  common: { welcome: "Welcome" },
  actions: { submit: "Submit" },
  profile: { greeting: "Hello, {{name}}!" }
}
```

**tRPC Data Fetching**

Mobile uses tRPC React Query with MMKV persistence:

```typescript
import { trpc } from "@/services/trpc/trpc";

export const HoldingsList: FC = () => {
  const { themed } = useAppTheme();
  const { data, isLoading, refetch } = trpc.holdings.getWithDetails.useQuery();

  if (isLoading) return <LoadingSpinner />;

  return (
    <FlatList
      data={data}
      renderItem={({ item }) => <HoldingItem item={item} />}
      refreshControl={
        <RefreshControl refreshing={isLoading} onRefresh={refetch} />
      }
    />
  );
};
```

**Expo Router Navigation**

File-based routing with typed routes:

```typescript
// app/(tabs)/index.tsx - Home tab
export default function HomeScreen() {
  return <View>{/* Content */}</View>;
}

// Navigate programmatically
import { useRouter } from "expo-router";

const router = useRouter();
router.push("/account/123");
router.replace("/auth");
```

## Naming Conventions

### General Rules

- **Component files**: PascalCase (`AccountCard.tsx`, `Button.tsx`)
- **Other files**: camelCase (`authUtils.ts`, `tokenService.ts`)
- **Variables/functions**: camelCase (`getUserAccounts`, `totalBalance`)
- **Constants/map keys**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_RETRY_COUNT`, `API_TIMEOUT`)

### Backend Specific

- **Services**: PascalCase with suffix (`AccountService`, `PricingService`)
- **Repositories**: PascalCase with suffix (`UserRepository`, `HoldingRepository`)
- **Use Cases**: PascalCase with suffix (`CreateHoldingUseCase`, `ImportWalletUseCase`)
- **Entities**: PascalCase (`Account`, `Holding`, `Token`)

### Frontend Specific

- **React Components**: PascalCase function names (`function AccountList()`)
- **Hooks**: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useAuth`, `useAccounts`)
- **Context values**: camelCase (`userContext`, `themeContext`)

### Mobile Specific

- **Screens**: PascalCase with `Screen` suffix (`WelcomeScreen.tsx`, `DashboardScreen.tsx`)
- **Theme files**: camelCase (`colors.ts`, `spacing.ts`, `typography.ts`)
- **Translation files**: lowercase language code (`en.ts`, `ru.ts`)
- **Translation keys**: `namespace:key` format (`common:welcome`, `auth:signIn`)
- **Style constants**: `$` prefix with camelCase (`$container`, `$title`, `$submitButton`)

## Code Quality Standards

### TypeScript Requirements

- **Strict mode MUST be enabled** in all tsconfig.json files
- **No `any` types** except where explicitly justified with comment
- **Explicit return types** for public functions and methods
- **Type-safe validation** using Zod schemas aligned with TypeScript types

### Linting & Formatting

**Backend & Web Frontend:**

- Use Biome.js for linting and formatting
- Run `bun run lint` before committing
- All warnings must be resolved

**Mobile:**

- Use ESLint with Expo config
- Run `yarn lint:fix` before committing
- No emoji in code or comments

### Testing Requirements

- **93%+ test coverage** must be maintained
- **Unit tests** for all business logic and utilities
- **Integration tests** for repositories and use cases with real database
- **Type tests** for Zod schemas
- **Financial calculations** must have edge case tests (negatives, precision, large numbers)
- **TDD encouraged** - write failing tests first when practical

### Logging Standards

**Backend:**

```typescript
import { createComponentLogger } from "@/infrastructure/logging";

const logger = createComponentLogger("AccountService");

logger.info("Account created", { accountId, userId });
logger.error("Failed to create account", { error, input });
logger.debug("Processing account", { details });
```

**Mobile:**

```typescript
// Use Reactotron in development
if (__DEV__) {
  console.tron.log("Data fetched", data);
}

// Never log sensitive data
console.log(user.email); // ❌ BAD
console.log({ userId: user.id }); // ✅ GOOD
```

### Mobile-Specific Quality Rules

- **NO inline styles** - all styles must use ThemedStyle pattern
- **NO hardcoded colors/spacing** - use theme tokens
- **NO hardcoded user-facing text** - use tx props with translation keys
- **NO translate() function** when component supports tx prop
- **NO emoji** in code, comments, or user-facing text
- **ALL translations** must exist in both en.ts and ru.ts

